Robert Fiske (actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Fiske_(actor) 0 Robert Fiske (20 October 1889 – 12 September 1944) was an American film actor during the 1930s and 1940s. Born in Griggsville, Missouri he appeared in 66 films, primarily B-movies and westerns. He died in Sunland, California of congestive heart failure at the age of 54 and was buried at Forest Lawn Glendale, Glendale, California.
